<main class="sfdx-slim slds-card">

  <h2 class="slds-text-heading_medium slds-p-top_medium slds-p-bottom_large">Want to try your own repo?</h2>
  
  <p class="slds-p-bottom_medium">It's easy. Just use the <img src="/dist/assets/images/DeployToSFDX.svg" /> button.</p>

  <p class="slds-p-bottom_medium">Add the following source to your github repo (making sure to change the <code>template</code> to your repository:</p>
  
  <div class="slds-card sfdx-code" readonly>[![Deploy](https://deploy-to-sfdx.com/dist/assets/images/DeployToSFDX.svg)](https://deploy-to-sfdx.com/deploy?template=https://github.com/wadewegner/sfdx-simple)</div>

  <p class="slds-p-top_medium slds-p-bottom_medium">Next, create a <code>.salesforcedx.yaml</code> file in your repo:</p>

<div class="slds-card sfdx-code" readonly>scratch-org-def: config/project-scratch-def.json
assign-permset: false
run-apex-tests: false
delete-scratch-org: false
show-scratch-org-url: true
</div>
    
  <p class="slds-p-top_medium slds-p-bottom_medium">That's it! See the <a href="https://github.com/wadewegner/sfdx-simple/" target="_blank">https://github.com/wadewegner/sfdx-simple</a> for an example of the button in action!</p>

